<h1>Cornered Image Box</h1>
<p>A corner image placed in each corner of a box, all done in CSS only.</p>

<h2>Usage</h2>
<p>Usage is pretty straightforward:</p>

<ul>
<li>Add the rules from the style.css to your own stylesheet.</li>
<li>place the image named in a directory named (or change box-holder class to 
reflect the accurate filename and path of your image).</li>
<li>Create a div and assign the the css class named <em>inner-content</em> to it.</li>
<li>With in that div, create another div and give it the class name <em>boxHolder</em></li>
<li>Feel free to change the width and colors of inner-content class to suit your needs but the
min-height should be left as is.</li>
</ul>

</body>
